4.12	Karl_Binding	Karl Binding	Karl Ludwig Lorenz Binding (April 6, 1841 â€“ April 7, 1920) was a German jurist known as a promoter of the theory of retributive justice. His influential book, Die Freigabe der Vernichtung Lebensunwertem Lebens ("Allowing the Destruction of Life Unworthy of Living"), written together with the psychiatrist Alfred Hoche, was used by the Nazis to justify their T-4 Euthanasia Program.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/8/80/Karl_Binding.jpeg
